        "uranium": "Uranium"
    },
    {
        " fission": "Nuclear Fission"
    },
    {
        ", providing a high neutron flux and the highest available sensitivities for most elements. The neutron flux from such a reactor is in the order of 10 12 neutrons cm −2 s −1 . Pollard, A. M., Heron, C., 1996, Archaeological Chemistry. Cambridge, Royal Society of Chemistry. The type of neutrons generated are of relatively low ": null
    },
