        " type. Of these the scintillation and semiconductor type are the most widely employed. There are two detector configurations utilised, they are the planar detector, used for PGNAA and the well detector, used for DGNAA. The planar detector has a flat, large collection surface area and can be placed close to the sample. The well detector ‘surrounds’ the sample with a large collection surface area.     Scintillation-type detectors use a radiation-sensitive crystal, most commonly thallium-doped sodium iodide , which emits light when struck by gamma photons. These detectors have excellent sensitivity and stability, and a reasonable resolution.     Semiconductor detectors utilise the semiconducting element ": null
